[Johnny is seen on T.V.]
Johnny: This just in. [shows a silent clip of SpongeBob riding the Big One with Patrick, Squidward, and Mr. Krabs while playing JKL's drums from "SpongeBob SquarePants vs. The Big One"] SpongeBob always treats the ocean fair and square but he needs your help. So here are some simple ways that SpongeBob and you can help save the big blue.
[clip from "SpongeBob Meets the Stranger" plays]
Johnny: [during clip] Look out for litter and pick up garbage before it enters the ocean.
SpongeBob: [in clip] Where is all this litter coming from?!
[clip from "Boating School" plays]
Johnny: [during clip] Muffle the motor. Turning off boat engines keeps harmful chemicals out of the water.
[shows a silent clip of Patrick and SpongeBob cleaning the beach with a dustpan and broom from "Sand Castles in the Sand"]
Johnny: [during clip] And slash the trash.
[shows scissors cutting six-pack soda rings]
Johnny: [during clip] Cutting six-pack soda rings can save the lives of countless marine animals. For more ways SpongeBob and you can save the big blue, go to nick.com/biggreenhelp.
